# Cognivest — backend environment template
#
# The backend does NOT maintain its own environment variables. All configuration
# is inherited from the repository-root `.env` (template: ../.env.example), which
# is loaded by `src/config/settings.py` (Pydantic BaseSettings).
#
# To configure locally:
#   1. Copy the root template:  cp ../.env.example ../.env
#   2. Fill in secrets in ../.env  (it is git-ignored — NEVER commit it).
#
# See ../.env.example for the full, authoritative list of variables:
#   APP_ENV, LOG_LEVEL, API_V1_PREFIX, BACKEND_CORS_ORIGINS,
#   DATABASE_URL, REDIS_URL, CELERY_BROKER_URL, CELERY_RESULT_BACKEND,
#   JWT_*, SERVICE_TOKEN, LLM_PROVIDER, LLM_MODEL, LLM_API_KEY, EMBEDDING_*,
#   MARKET_DATA_*, NEWS_API_*, WEB_SEARCH_*, QUERY_RATE_LIMIT_PER_MINUTE, ...
